	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I quibble with the poster(s) who say the guide isn't useful after the mid-upper 30's or isn't useful in dungeons.<BR>
<BR>
The strategies recommended are for the most part still working in the 50's in places like Kael, WL, Chardok, HS, etc.  And I've seen them work in the planes.<BR>
<BR>
Obviously there are adjustments to be made, esp. on dungeon raids w/ multiple groups.<BR>
<BR>
Re Main Assist not switching targets: when the Add is a caster and the original pull is not the MA should switch... Having announced if possible the switch.<BR>
<BR>
A treatise on appropriate hotkeys w/ %T might be a helpful addition here.<BR>
<BR>
Everyone else of course needs to KEEP hitting their hotkey that says /assist &lt;name&gt; throughout the battle just in case the announcement of target switch got lost in battle spam.<BR>
<BR>
And unless you're desperate for logs, turn off most of the battle spam; keep only what you need to do your own job better.<BR>
<BR>
Regarding group balance: yes, my ideal group would have a chanter or bard for crowd control, esp. in dungeons.  Some places we won't go unless we have a chanter/bard with us.  However, when you've been together as long as our group has, even bizarre combinations work most places.  We are 2 rangers, 2 druids, a cleric and a mage. Not many places we won't go... but that's also b/c we know how to use a 7-member team properly. Mage pets at 55+ are truly amazing tanks, can be ComHealed, and if they gack, mage sqeezes out another one :) Druids can SupHeal the dangerrangers... <BR>
<BR>
OH YES... one quibble w/ the original writer!!  You do NOT need a wizzie for group evacs!! Can you say &quot;Druid&quot;?? &lt;BG&gt;  Depending on what we're doing either one or both druids mem evac spells.<BR>
<BR>
And finally, there *are* times, esp. in dungeons, where the tank DOES have to stay behind and keep fighting, even unto death.<BR>
<BR>
IF we're lucky, the evac'er can get the evac off. If the mob is pounding on the evac'er, tht won't happen. Better get the cleric OUT so he can come back and res one tank than let the cleric die so he has to come back in naked and res himself.<BR>
<BR>
Finally, for the 55+ game... mages are invaluable for another skill: Call of Heroes.  Until you've been Summoned by the Mage from the depths of the lava in which you're burning to death or the pit out of which you'll never climb before the monsters kill you, you don't know what salvation feels like.  It's also helpful in group movement if the mage can get to where the group needs to be safely.<BR>
<BR>
Group leader can bind outside dungeon. Gate out, group the new group member, zone in; get summoned to group. Awesome :D<BR>
<BR>
Thanks for the great strategy guide and for the additions from most of you folks :)  Ss battle strategist for my guild I&quot;ve already posted the link on our guild site.<BR>
<BR>
Wolana Phoenixfyre, druid, Kelethin-Xegony<BR>
Knight General, Soldiers of Fortune, in service to her majesty Queen Jalea 52 seasons
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
