	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I think this guide is very very well written, and the information is great! A lot of us higher level people know this, but you'd be surprised at the ones that don't. I have grouped with a lot of people in the past that just don't know how do pull. Point and case, once, in Lower Guk at the Frenzied camp, our monk got really ambitious and pulled 14+ frogs, then thought itd be smart to FD BEFORE saying gate, getting ALL us casters killed. Another time in Lower Guk we had a necro that wanted to pull with the tank, so we had like 8 mobs per pull because the necro wouldn't stick to his roll. And another time still in Lower Guk the SK of the group ran straight into a room he &quot;thought&quot; was empty, bringing back one helluva train. Wow, Lower Guk has some bad pullers, hehe. Basically, the key to the group is knowing your puller, and having the puller know the groups ability. I find it best to have monks pull, the ones I group with have a REALLY nice ac and resists for casters, and can easily FD overpulls if we dont have an enchanter. My 2cp on a perfect group is as follows-<BR>
<BR>
Shaman(myself)- GREAT slow spells for those high level mobs that barsh really hard, back up heals, and excellent regen spells, and can follow up with DoT's and DD's, etc, and their pet can help tank, a jack of all trades =)<BR>
<BR>
Enchanter- NEEDED for high level groups. They can mez, give mana regens(gotta love C and C2... drool) to keep casters on non stop full mana, magic debuff so the slower can land his spell, help DD if needed, etc.<BR>
<BR>
Monk- NEEDED for pulling, can be the best puller if they know what they are doing, and can deal lots of damage really quick, if they have high AC it can save on heals, plus the mend acts like an extra heal to save the Cleric or Shamans mana.<BR>
<BR>
Cleric- Main healer, Complete heal is a must in high level groups unless you have 2 good shaman going. Rez's are a plus in case of deaths.<BR>
<BR>
Warrior or SK- your main damage dealer, lots of damage and high AC equal quick killing with little life lost. If you have an SK the extra spells help and the HT is a plus in case of sticky situations.<BR>
<BR>
Wiz or Necro- Both good DD's and the DoTs from the necros help a lot. Necro pets are excellent tanks at high levels, and really help the killing. The wizards very powerful DD's always help out, but aggros can be sticky if they dont let the tanks get some damage in first.<BR>
<BR>
This list is based on a Dark team group on a PvP server, so for a light team or Blue server the group would be different with rangers, druids, etc. I dont find myself grouping with Rogues alot, but they are a plus with Backstabs and damage dealing, but are not necessary IMO. So that is an ideal group in my eyes. Hope this adds some help to the guide, which once again, was very well written, grats! Take care guys.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Sorsisis Plaguescale, Officer of Second Rising<BR>
45 Shaman on Tallon Zek
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
